''See also [[évidence]]''
==English==

===Noun===
'''evidence''' (uncountable)

#[[Fact]]s or [[observation]]s presented in support of an [[assertion]].
#''(legal)'' Anything admitted by a [[court]] to prove or disprove alleged matters of fact in a [[trial]].

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[osoitus]] (1), [[todiste]] (2), [[näyttö]] (2), [[todistusaineisto]] (2)
*French: [[Preuve]] ''f''
*German: [[Beweis]] ''m''
*Spanish: [[Evidencia]] ''f''

===Verb===
'''to evidence''' (transitive)

#To provide evidence for, or suggest the truth of:
#:''She was furious, as evidenced by her slamming the door.''

